<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-017-510  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 017 510.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  Jan 1 1990 n571 p33(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Trying times ahead for test market. (test and measurementindustry)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Ryan, Margaret.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The test and measurement industry will experience slower growth inthe coming years due to uncertainty in the defense industry.andO;Analysts say that defense firms are feeling the pinch of reducedgovernment spending and are in turn reducing their research anddevelopment budgets, which is causing reduced demand, particularlyfor microwave-related equipment.andP;  In 1989, the industry grew at 6percent, about 2 percentage points less than in 1988.andP;  Projectedgrowth for 1990 is 4 to 5 percent in the US market and 8 percentworldwide.andP;  Further reductions in defence spending could slowgrowth even more.andP;  Despite these predictions, some market segmentswill experience healthy growth, such as those for digitaloscilloscopes and logic analyzers.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Test EquipmentMeasurementMarket AnalysisSales AnalysisForecasting.andO;Feature:   illustrationgraphphotograph.andO;Caption:   Worldwide Tandamp;M sales inch along. (graph)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>